21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 5-60-102 is repealed.
22 5-60-102. Prohibition on sales and distribution of novelty lighters.
23 (a)(1) As used in this section, “novelty lighter” means a product
24 commonly used by consumers to ignite cigarettes, cigars, pipes, gas grills,
25 or other combustible material that has entertaining audio or visual features
26 that depict or resemble in physical form or function articles commonly
27 recognized as appealing to or intended for use by children ten (10) years of
28 age or younger, including without limitation lighters that depict or resemble
29 cartoon characters, toys, guns, watches, musical instruments, vehicles, toy
30 animals, food, or beverages or that play musical notes or have flashing
31 lights or other entertaining features.
32 (2) “Novelty lighter” does not include:
33 (A) A lighter manufactured before 1980; or
34 (B) A lighter that lacks a device necessary to produce
35 combustion or a flame.
36 (b)(1) The retail sale, offer of retail sale, gift, or distribution of
